label.value: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration

value.value: Actividad o concentración anormal de enzimas hepáticas

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration

value.value: 肝酵素活性または濃度の異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration

definition.value: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in liver tissue.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la urocanasa hepática.
肝ウロカナーゼ活性の低下
Activity of urocanase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.
Deterioro de la hidrólisis del sulfato de cerebrósido
硫酸セレブロシドの加水分解障害

Reduced hydrolysis (splitting of a bond and the addition of the hydrogen anion of water) of the sulfuric ester linkage in the molecule of cerebroside sulfate, possibly leading to accumuation of cerebroside sulfate.

definition.value: This feature can be assayed by cerebroside sulfate loading tests of cultured dermal fibroblasts.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la glutaril-CoA oxidasa peroxisomal
ペルオキシソームグルタリル-CoAオキシダーゼ活性の低下

Diminished enzyme activity of peroxisomal glutaryl-CoA oxidase, an enzyme that metabolizes glutaryl-CoA (a metabolite of L-lysine, L-hydroxy-lysine and L-tryptophan) by dehydrogenation to glutaconyl-CoA directly followed by decarboxylation of this to crotonyl-CoA.
Disminución de la actividad del esterol 27-hidroxilasa
ステロール27-ヒドロキシラーゼ活性の低下

Diminished activity of the enzyme sterol 27-hydroxylase, which participates in the degradation of cholesterol to bile acid. Sterol 27-hydroxylase catalyzes the first step in the normal oxidation of the steroid side chain, converting cholesterol, as well as different 7a-hydroxylated cholesterol metabolites, to 27-oxygenated steroids.
Disminución de la actividad de la acil-CoA deshidrogenasa de cadena corta
短鎖アシル-CoAデヒドロゲナーゼ活性の低下
Diminished activity of the enzyme Short-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (SCAD), a key enzyme of fatty acid beta-oxidation that catalyzes the first step in mitochondrial beta-oxidation of fatty acids.
3-ホスホグリセリン酸デヒドロゲナーゼ活性の低下
Disminución de la actividad de la 3-fosfoglicerato deshidrogenasa

Diminished activity of the enzyme 3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase (PGDH), which catalyzes the first step in the pathway by converting D-3-phosphoglycerate (PGA), an intermediate in glycolysis, to phosphohydroxypyruvate concomitant with the reduction of NAD+.
Mitocondrias alargadas
ミトコンドリアの伸長
Increase in length of mitochondria.

definition.value: Mitochondrial elongation can be initiated by a gradual merge of the outer mitochondrial membranes of two individual mitochondria.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la metionina adenosiltransferasa hepática
肝メチオニンアデノシルトランスフェラーゼ活性の低下
Activity of methionine adenosyltransferase in the liver below the lower limit of normal. Note that there are multiple methionine adenosyltransferase isoezymes.
Pérdida de neuronas dopaminérgicas de sustancia negra
黒質ドーパミン作動性ニューロンの減少
Degeneration and loss of neurons in the substantia nigra of the brain.

definition.value: Ppigmented neurons in the substantia nigra produce the neurotransmitter dopamine. The loss of these neurons leads to the classical motor symptoms of Parkinson disease. The pigment contained within these neurons, termed neuromelanin because of its similar appearance to cutaneous melanin, is so abundant in the substantia nigra of the human brain that this structure can be seen macroscopically as a darkened area (hence the origin of the name given to this brain region)

value.value: Lipoma intramuscular
筋内脂肪腫

definition.value: A lipoma that is located within a muscle.

value.value: Telangiectasia cutánea
皮膚毛細血管拡張症

definition.value: Dilated blood vessels on the skin.

value.value: Actividad anormal de la aromatasa
アロマターゼ活性異常

definition.value: Aromatase activity outside of the normal range.

value.value: Aromatase is a specific component of the cytochrome P450 enzyme system responsible for the transformation of androgen precursors into estrogens. This enzyme is encoded by the CYP19A1 gene located at chromosome 15q21.2, that is, expressed in ovary and testis, but also in many extraglandular sites such as the placenta, brain, adipose tissue, and bone.
Aumento de la actividad de la aromatasa
アロマターゼ活性上昇

definition.value: Enzyme activity of aromatase above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la aromatasa
アロマターゼ活性低下

definition.value: Enzyme activity of aromatase below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Amiloidosis corneal
角膜アミロイドーシス

definition.value: A form of amyloidosis that is located in the cornea.

value.value: Morfología anormal de los queratinocitos
角質細胞の形態異常
Any structural anomaly of the keratinocyte. The keratinocyte is the major cell type of the epidermis and is responsible for generating the protective barrier.
Vacuolización de queratinocitos
角質細胞の空胞化

definition.value: Increased number of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in keratinocytes.

value.value: Adenocarcinoma de glándula parótida
耳下腺腺がん

definition.value: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the parotid gland.

value.value: Vasculitis pulmonar
肺血管炎
Cellular inflammation, vessel destruction, and tissue necrosis of the blood vessels of the lung.
Disminución de la actividad de la D-glicerato quinasa hepática
肝D-グリセリンキナーゼ活性低下
Activity of D-glycerate kinase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.
Hemofagocitosis de ganglios linfáticos
リンパ節血球貪食症
Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages in a lymph node.

definition.value: See Figure 1 of PMID:16859547.

value.value: Hipoplasia de la rama púbica superior
上恥骨端低形成
Underdevelopment of the upper branch of the pubis bone (inferior pubic ramus).
Adenofibroma uterino
子宮腺線維腫

definition.value: A rare benign mullerian mixed tumor of the uterus composed of benign epithelial and mesenchymal components.

value.value: Hamartoma pulmonar
肺過誤腫

A benign malformation of the lung that includes an abnormal mixture of tissue components such as cartilage, epithelium, fat, or muscle which are common to the lung but without preservation of the organ architecture.
Distensión axonal periférica
末梢性軸索膨張症
An abnormal histological finding characterized by an increase in the cross-section area of peripheral nerve axons (up to 20-25 micrometers in diameter).

definition.value: In giant axonal neuropathy, distended axons are observed in conjunction with thin myelin sheaths. Distended axons may be filled with masses of neurofilaments. See Figures 4 and 5 of PMID:15897506.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad alfa-manosidasa
α-マンノシダーゼ活性低下

definition.value: Concentration or activity of alpha mannosidase below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

value.value: Morfología anormal de los hepatocitos
肝細胞形態異常

definition.value: A structural anomaly of the hepatocyte, which is the main cell type that makes up the liver perncyhma. Hepatocytes are usually binucleated and appear as sheets in the liver tissue.

value.value: Pigmentación lisosomal similar a la melanina hepática
肝メラニン様リソソーム色素沈着

definition.value: Accumulation of dark, coarsely granular pigment localized in lysosomes of centrilobular hepatocytes.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la uroporfirinógeno descarboxilasa
ウロポルフィリノーゲン脱炭酸酵素活性の低下

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase (UROD; EC 4.1.1.37) below the lower limit of normal.
Uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase low

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la hemo oxigenasa.
ヘムオキシゲナーゼ活性の低下

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme heme oxygenase below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Neuronas acromáticas inflamadas en la corteza cerebral

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Swollen achromatic neurons in the cerebral cortex

label.value: Swollen achromatic neurons in the cerebral cortex

value.value: 大脳皮質の無色素性ニューロンの腫脹

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Swollen achromatic neurons in the cerebral cortex

value.value: The presence of enlarged and swollen neurons that lack Nissl bodies (the rough endoplasmic reticulum-achromasia refers to neurons that lack Nissl bodies) in the cortex of the brain.
Hepatocitos vacuolados
肝細胞の空胞化

definition.value: Presence of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in hepatocytes, which normally rarely contain vacuoles.

value.value: Falta de formación de pronúcleo de ovocitos
卵子前核形成の欠如

An abnormality of oocyte maturation characterized by the inability of oocytes to form pronuclei after in vitro fertilization procedures. Oocytes normally show two pronuclei 17 to 20 hours after in vitro insemination.
Epitelioma escamoso autocurativo
Epitelioma squamoso autorigenerante
Selbstheilendes Plattenepitheliom
自己修復性扁平上皮腫
A type of skin tumor that initially presents as a reddish macule and subsequently becomes papular, enlarged, ulcerated and ultimately heals leaving pitted scars.

definition.value: Individuals with pathogenic variants in TGFBR1 may present with multiple self-healing squamous epitheliomas. See Figure 1 of PMID:33256177.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de ácido pristánico circulante
循環プリスタン酸濃度の上昇
Concentration of pristanic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
Cuerpos sarcoplásmicos
小胞体

definition.value: Rounded or oval structures that appeared brown on hematoxylin and eosin and red on the modified Gomori trichrome stain.
The sarcoplasm is the cytoplasm of a muscle cell.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de hidroxiprolina en el LCR
CSFヒドロキシプロリン濃度の上昇

definition.value: Concentration of hydroxyproline in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: CSFシスチン濃度の低下
Disminución de la concentración de cistina en el LCR

definition.value: Concentration of cystine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal. Cystine is sulfur-containing amino acid obtained by the oxidation of two cysteine molecules which are then linked via a disulfide bond.

value.value: Actividad anormal de la beta-manosidasa
β-マンノシダーゼ活性異常

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase outside normal limits. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides.

value.value: Aumento de la actividad de beta-manosidasa
β-マンノシダーゼ活性の上昇

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase above the upper limit of normal. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la alfa-L-fucosidasa
α-L-フコシダーゼ活性の低下

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Actividad anormal de alfa-L-fucosidasa
α-L-フコシダーゼ活性異常

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la actividad de alfa-L-fucosidasa
α-L-フコシダーゼ活性上昇

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración circulante de S-adenosil-L-homocisteína
循環S-アデノシル-L-ホモシステイン濃度の上昇
Increased concentration of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine in the blood circulation.
Aumento de la concentración de S-adenosil-L-metionina
血中S-アデノシル-L-メチオニン濃度の上昇

definition.value: Concentration S-adenosyl-L-methionine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Hipertermia maligna provocada por el ejercicio
運動誘発性悪性高熱症

definition.value: Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by exercise-induced life-threatening hyperthermia with a body temperature over 40 degrees C and signs of encephalopathy ranging from confusion to convulsions or coma. Incidence increases with rising ambient temperature and relative humidity. Manifestations may include rhabdomyolysis (presenting with myalgia, muscle weakness, and myoglobinuria), tachycardia, and in severe cases multiorgan failure.

value.value: Hipertermia maligna desencadenada por anestesia
麻酔薬誘発性悪性高熱症

definition.value: Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by a rapid increase in temperature to 39-42 degrees C in response to inhalational anesthetics such as halothane or to muscle relaxants such as succinylcholine.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de ácido argininosuccínico en el LCR
CSFアルギニノコハク酸濃度の上昇

definition.value: Concentration of argininosuccinic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de aspartilglucosamina en el LCR
アスパルチルグルコサミンCSF濃度の上昇

definition.value: Concentration of aspartylglucosamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.
Aspartylglucosamine is a derivative of aspartic acid.
